  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Finance Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Independently manage the full set of accounts, ensuring timely and accurate closing and reporting to meet Group deadlines.</li></ul><ul><li>Oversee the billing process for Singapore and regional projects, including invoicing at various stages of project completion.</li></ul><ul><li>Manage payments, ensure accurate reporting, and track billing schedules in line with project milestones and work in process schedules.</li></ul><ul><li>Monitor and supervise fixed assets, including depreciation calculations and verifying the integrity and existence of assets.</li></ul><ul><li>Assist in preparing audit schedules and liaising with auditors as necessary.</li></ul><ul><li>Liaise with banks, company secretary, auditors, and tax agents for administrative and statutory matters.</li></ul><ul><li>Handle any other ad-hoc finance and administrative duties as assigned by the immediate supervisor, manager, or management.</li></ul><p>Requirements: </p><ul><li><p>Candidate must possess at least a Diploma/Partial ACCA in Finance, Accountancy or equivalent. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>At least 3 years of relevant working experience in a similar role. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Knowledge of accounting software (A2000 Solutions) and regional taxes is an added advantage. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Meticulous and responsible team player with excellent organizational, problem solving, communication and interpersonal skills. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Highly motivated and takes initiative to take up new challenges </p></li></ul><p>For further enquiries or submission, you may reach out to Luna (HR Executive) at Luna.cheok@sg.rlb.com</p>",
